  <p>When working through beginner films, do not worry about understanding every word. Your goal at this stage is to get comfortable with the rhythm and melody of spoken Mandarin. Pay attention to how characters greet each other, how they express agreement or disagreement, and how their tone of voice changes depending on who they are talking to. Animated films like Big Fish and Begonia are especially useful because the narration tends to be slower and more clearly enunciated than dialogue in live-action films. Comedies like Lost on Journey use physical humor and visual gags that help you follow the story even when the language moves too fast.</p>

